<v Nathaniel>It includes ontotheology, inscribing it and exceeding it within return.</v>

01:07:17.400 --> 01:07:34.420
<v Nathaniel>I mean, that's a pretty key difference is, like, at least in its most common understandings, a negative theology is basically trying to say, like, look, the finitude of all of these concepts fail to get at the super-essentiality of God.</v>

01:07:34.420 --> 01:07:46.580
<v Nathaniel>It's like, you know, it's like, we're not just, this is the ontological distinction, is that, like, God is the beingness of being, not just, like, a particular being.</v>

01:07:46.580 --> 01:07:58.120
